      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's kind of you to say, but it doesn't feel that way. Every time they come over, I see them looking at the medicine bottles or seeing how much I struggle to get around the house. I can see the exhaustion in their eyes. It's like they're just performing their duty, and honestly, I hate that I'm the reason they're tired. Wouldn't it be easier for everyone if they didn't have to worry about me anymore?",
